net.opentsdb.uid

类 UniqueIdFilterPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.opentsdb.uid.UniqueIdFilterPlugin
  • 直接已知子类:
    UniqueIdWhitelistFilter

    public abstract class UniqueIdFilterPlugin
extends Object
    A filter that can determine whether or not UIDs should be allowed assignment based on their metric and tags. This is useful for such situations as:
    • Enforcing naming standards
    • Blacklisting certain names or properties
    • Preventing cardinality explosions
    Note: Implementations must have a parameterless constructor. The initialize(TSDB) method will be called immediately after the plugin is instantiated and before any other methods are called.
    从以下版本开始:
    2.3

      • initialize

        public abstract void initialize(TSDB tsdb)
        Called by TSDB to initialize the plugin Implementations are responsible for setting up any IO they need as well as starting any required background threads. Note: Implementations should throw exceptions if they can't start up properly. The TSD will then shutdown so the operator can fix the problem. Please use IllegalArgumentException for configuration issues.
        参数:
        tsdb - The parent TSDB object
        抛出:
        IllegalArgumentException - if required configuration parameters are missing
        RuntimeException - if something else goes wrong

      • shutdown

        public abstract com.stumbleupon.async.Deferred<Object> shutdown()
        Called to gracefully shutdown the plugin. Implementations should close any IO they have open
        返回:
        A deferred object that indicates the completion of the request. The Object has not special meaning and can be null (think of it as Deferred<Void>).

      • version

        public abstract String version()
        Should return the version of this plugin in the format: MAJOR.MINOR.MAINT, e.g. "2.3.1". The MAJOR version should match the major version of OpenTSDB the plugin is meant to work with.
        返回:
        A version string used to log the loaded version

      • collectStats

        public abstract void collectStats(StatsCollector collector)
        Called by the TSD when a request for statistics collection has come in. The implementation may provide one or more statistics. If no statistics are available for the implementation, simply stub the method.
        参数:
        collector - The collector used for emitting statistics

      • allowUIDAssignment

        public abstract com.stumbleupon.async.Deferred<Boolean> allowUIDAssignment(UniqueId.UniqueIdType type,
                                                                           String value,
                                                                           String metric,
                                                                           Map<String,String> tags)
        Determine whether or not the UID should be assigned. If the UID should not be assigned a value, the implementation can return false or an exception in the deferred object. Otherwise it should return true and the UID will proceed with assignment. NOTE: In some cases the metric and tags may be null, particularly if the synchronous APIs were called. In such a situation, make sure the implementation handles it properly.
        参数:
        type - The type of UID being assigned
        value - The string value of the UID
        metric - The metric name associated with the UID for assignment
        tags - The tag set associated with the UID
        返回:
        True if the UID should be assigned, false if not.

      • fillterUIDAssignments

        public abstract boolean fillterUIDAssignments()
        Whether or not the filter should process UIDs.
        返回:
        True if #allowUIDAssignment(UniqueIdType, String, String, Map) should be called, false if not.
